# Brutalist Archival Index

## Source of Truth: Neo-Brutalism & Archival Aesthetic

*Reference Sites: dau.lt, Are.na, brutalistwebsites.com*

---

## 1. Design DNA: "The Raw Material"

### Core Philosophy

**"Honesty of Material."** Do not hide the browser. Embrace the raw, unadorned nature of HTML/CSS.

### Fundamental Rules

- **No Blur.** No CSS `filter: blur()` or `backdrop-filter: blur()`.
- **No Shadows.** No `box-shadow`, `text-shadow`, or any shadow effects.
- **No Rounded Corners.** No `border-radius`. Everything is a box with sharp, 90-degree corners.
- **Everything is a Box.** Every element must have a `1px solid` border (`1px solid black` or `1px solid currentColor`).

### Color System

```css
:root {
  --bg-canvas: #FFFFFF;      /* Paper - default light */
  /* OR */
  --bg-canvas: #000000;      /* Void - dark mode */
  
  --text-primary: #000000;   /* Contrast with bg-canvas */
  /* OR */
  --text-primary: #FFFFFF;   /* For dark mode */
  
  --accent: #0000FF;         /* Hyper-Link Blue */
  /* OR */
  --accent: #FF0000;         /* Warning Red */
}

/* Constraint: No gradients. Only solid, flat colors. */
```

### Border System

```css
/* All elements must have borders */
* {
  border: 1px solid currentColor;
  /* OR */
  border: 1px solid black;
}

/* Exceptions: body, html can be borderless */
body, html {
  border: none;
}
```

