## 7. Accessibility

### High Contrast

Brutalism naturally provides high contrast, but ensure:

```css
/* Minimum contrast ratios per WCAG */
:root {
  --bg-canvas: #FFFFFF;
  --text-primary: #000000;
  /* Contrast ratio: 21:1 (AAA) */
}

/* Dark mode */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root {
    --bg-canvas: #000000;
    --text-primary: #FFFFFF;
    /* Contrast ratio: 21:1 (AAA) */
  }
}
```

### Screen Reader Considerations

#### ASCII Art / Raw Layouts

When using ASCII art or purely visual layouts, provide alternative text:

```jsx
<div className="ascii-art" aria-hidden="true">
  {asciiContent}
</div>
<div className="sr-only">
  {descriptionText}
</div>
```

```css
.sr-only {
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
  height: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border-width: 0;
}
```

#### Semantic HTML

```jsx
<nav aria-label="Main navigation">
  <ul role="list">
    <li>
      <a href="/project-1">Project One</a>
    </li>
  </ul>
</nav>

<main>
  <article>
    <h1>Project Title</h1>
    <time dateTime="2024-01-01">2024-01-01</time>
  </article>
</main>
```

#### Keyboard Navigation

```css
/* Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible */
a:focus,
button:focus {
  outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Remove default focus styles only if custom ones are provided */
*:focus {
  outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

#### Motion Preferences

```css
/* Respect reduced motion preferences */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *,
  *::before,
  *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
  
  .ticker-content {
    animation: none;
  }
}
```

